        <p><strong>Cristiano Ronaldo,</strong>(born Feb. 5, 1985, Funchal, Madeira, Port.), Portuguese football (soccer) player.
            While playing with Manchester United (2003–09), he developed into one of the game’s best forwards,
             noted for his free-reined attacking style.<a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Europe">Europe</a> leading scorer,
              with 31 League goals. He is the all-time leading scorer for <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Spain">Spain</a> 
              <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Real-Madrid">Real Madrid</a>.

